**Version Used**: 2015, 15

```C#
class C {
	int x;
	C P { get; } = new C {  };
}
```

Inside the last pair of braces, IntelliSense should show `P`, to allow `new C { P = { x = 2 } }` (which is completely legal).

It currently only shows writable properties and concrete collection properties.

